# Smoke-fixture N-Triples input for `cargo run -p xtask -- verify`.
#
# Minimal, hand-audited. Picked for these properties:
#
# - Covers one IRI, one plain literal, one typed literal, one BNode,
#   one language-tagged literal — enough for the canonicalisation path
#   to disagree across shadows if canonicalisation is wrong.
# - Deliberately includes mixed ASCII-only and non-BMP characters (the
#   "Ünïcødé" literal + the U+1F600 😀) to exercise literal escaping.
# - No `@prefix` — this is pure N-Triples, so it survives the smallest
#   possible parser subset.
#
# Referenced by ADR-0020 §Acceptance ("`cargo run -p xtask -- verify`
# green on a smoke fixture"). Adding cases here is cheap; deleting or
# renaming them may shift CI semantics, so prefer additive edits.

<http://example.org/alice> <http://example.org/knows> <http://example.org/bob> .
<http://example.org/alice> <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/name> "Alice" .
<http://example.org/bob> <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/name> "Bøb Ünïcødé 😀"@en .
<http://example.org/alice> <http://example.org/age> "30"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer> .
_:carol <http://example.org/knows> <http://example.org/alice> .
